nd 3D animations.'),(3093,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_6_paragraph','field_533b304e3f665'),(3094,218,'content_solutions_page_content_7_headline','Original and Medically Reviewed'),(3095,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_7_headline','field_533b30573f668'),(3096,218,'content_solutions_page_content_7_paragraph','Our health literacy experts produce original content that is easily understood. All content is written at an 8th grade reading level and approved by Healthline’s team of medical professionals.'),(3097,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_7_paragraph','field_533b30573f669'),(3098,218,'content_solutions_page_content_8_headline','Partner Implementations'),(3099,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_8_headline','field_533b30693f66b'),(3100,218,'content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_0_image','292'),(3101,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_0_image','field_533b30a43f66d'),(3102,218,'content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_0_partner_logo','290'),(3103,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_0_partner_logo','field_533b30bc3f66e'),(3104,218,'content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_0_paragraph','Microsoft partnered with Healthline to create an anatomical search tool as part of the Bing Health and Fitness application, available via Windows 8.1. The tool is powered by Healthline’s unique taxonomy mappings that readily link body parts to related content, such as symptoms and conditions. Coupled with Healthline’s original health content that was provided in 17 languages, Healthline’s Taxonomy enabled Microsoft to provide an exceptional user experience for its global audience.'),(3105,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_0_paragraph','field_533b30cd3f66f'),(3106,218,'content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_1_image','304'),(3107,218,'_content_solutions_page_content_8_partner_implementations_1_image','field_533b30a43f66d'),(