earning.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMore information on Windows 8.1 is available at <a href=\"http://windows.microsoft.com\">http://windows.microsoft.com</a>.','Bringing the Microsoft Bing Health & Fitness App to Life for Windows 8.1','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2014-02-07 18:38:35','2014-02-07 18:38:35','',145,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/145-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(148,2,'2014-02-11 13:59:57','2014-02-11 13:59:57','<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">\"You\'ve Got This\" designed to give hope to individuals recently diagnosed with multiple sclerosis (MS).</h4>\r\nHealthline launched  a new public service initiative today with the goal of giving hope and advice to those who have been recently diagnosed with MS. “<a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\">You’ve Got This</a>” encourages people who are already moving their lives forward with MS to upload a video of themselves letting those with MS who are newly diagnosed know they are not alone and that they’ve “got this.” The videos will be posted on Healthline.com and shared with Healthline’s <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\"> Living with MS Facebook page</a>.\r\n\r\nIn addition to providing hope, participants should know that Healthline will donate $10 to the National MS Society for every video created, with a goal of donating $8,000 in total.\r\n\r\n“Many people who are faced with a recent diagnosis of MS feel frightened and alone,” said Tracy Rosecrans, Vice President of Marketing for Healthline’s Media Group. \"This initiative is meant to provide them with some hope and a feeling of community. They have a place to go to get some sound advice from those who are dealing with the disease themselves. The goal is to let them know that being newly diagnosed is the beginning of a new and different life and that they’ve got this.”\r\n\r\nAnyone can submit a “You’ve Got This” video. To participate, record a video, ideally lasting two minutes or less. Upload the video to Youtube, and send Healthline the URL. “Speak from your heart,” Rosecrans advises, “and imagine your good friend was recently diagnosed with MS. What would you say to them to make them feel better? What do you wish you had known when you were first diagnosed?”\r\n\r\n“We are most pleased to be a partner in You’ve Got This,” said Arney Rosenblat, Associate Vice President, Public Affairs at the National MS Society. “The initiative helps advance the Society’s mission of assisting people with MS live their best lives.”\r\n\r\nTo submit your video, view videos by others living with MS, and learn more visit: <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\">http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this</a>\r\n\r\n<b>About Healthline</b>\r\n\r\nSan Francisco-based Healthline is a leading provider of intelligent health information and technology solutions, enabling providers and everyday people to make more confident, informed healthcare decisions. The company\'s proprietary semantic health taxonomy platform powers a suite of marketing, health search, data-mining and content solutions for global enterprises and advertisers. Healthline is a Deloitte Technology Fast 500 company for the last four years. For more company information, visit <a title=\"corp.healthline.com\" href=\"http://corp.healthline.com\">corp.healthline.com</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>About the National MS Society</b>\r\n\r\nMS stops people from moving; the National MS Society exists to make sure it doesn’t. The Society addresses the challenges of each person affected by MS by funding cutting-edge research, driving change through advocacy, facilitating professional education, collaborating with MS organizations around the world, and providing programs and services designed to help people with MS and their families move forward with their lives. Learn more at <a href=\"http://www.nationalmssociety.org/\">http://www.nationalmssociety.org/</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Healthline Launches New Public Service Initiative with the National MS Society ','','publish','closed','closed','','healthline-launches-new-public-service-initiative-with-the-national-ms-society','','','2014-02-11 14:01:48','2014-02-11 14:01:48','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?post_type=press_release&#038;p=148',0,'press_release','',0),(151,11,'2014-02-11 19:27:43','2014-02-11 19:27:43','<h3>Rapidly-growing Healthline.com to help patient’s friends and families fundraise for life-changing medical expenses in time for the Holiday Season</h3>\r\n<strong>San Francisco, CA and Vancouver, BC – December 17, 2013</strong> – <a title=\"Healthline.com\" href=\"http://healthline.com\">Healthline</a> and <a title=\"FundRazr\" href=\"http://poweredby.fundrazr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">FundRazr</a> have teamed up to offer a new way to raise money online for patients with medical expenses in the U.S. or Internationally. <a title=\"Healthline Online Medical Fundraising\" href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/online-medical-fundraising\">Visitors to Healthline.com can now easily create personal crowdfunding campaigns</a>, share them on social media and email, and securely collect funds to help pay for medical expenses and gaps in insurance coverage.\r\n\r\n“Healthline is about guiding patients to better health, and our new crowdfunding feature, powered by FundRazr, helps address the pain many Americans face around often crushing medical expenses,” said David Kopp, EVP and GM of Healthline Media. “Our ability to bring medical crowdfunding to millions of people enables Americans to help give the gift of improved health and reduced stress to their loved ones.”\r\n\r\nMany Americans face medically-related financial stresses due to family accidents, chronic diseases, hospital bills, loss of income, or treatment and travel expenses.  In fact, medical bills are the leading cause of bankruptcies in the US with nearly 2 million people impacted.  Many others have gaps in insurance.  One study found that in 2010, 30 million Americans had medical bills in collection. Another study found that a full 40% of American adults have had <a title=\"Debt.org\" href=\"http://www.debt.org/medical/\" target=\"_blank\">trouble paying their medical bills</a>.<a title=\"\" href=\"#_edn1\">[i]</a>\r\n\r\nFundRazr has already helped tens of thousands of Americans help others, including Santa Cruz resident Sara Wysuph, who started a campaign for her brother-in-law, Jason Jones.  Jason was diagnosed with Acute Myeloid Leukemia in 2013. She found that her <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/crowdfunding-project?fr-campaign=0dUYc\">Jason Jones Medical Fund campaign</a> on FundRazr reached and built a community of caring behind their cause.\r\n\r\n“When Jason, a Deputy with the Santa Clara Sheriff’s Department and my brother-in-law, was diagnosed with Leukemia, he needed the support of his amazing community,” said Sara. “Thirty-three days running and over $31,000 was raised. We exceeded our goal and our expectations.  This is assurance that he will not go through this harrowing experience only to be drowned in debt. Thanks to FundRazr, and your continued support in tangible ways, he won’t be!”\r\n\r\nIn fact, crowdfunding is a rapidly growing fundraising method where many people contribute small amounts online to fund a campaign.  FundRazr is a global leader in crowd funding with more than $20M USD raised for medical crowdfunding alone.  Using a simple tool on Healthline.com, patients can now create campaigns for a friend, family member or themselves.  They can conveniently share their story on all the major social networks like Facebook or via email; post news and updates; and securely collect contributions via credit card, debit or PayPal.\r\n\r\n“We developed Powered by FundRazr from a real desire to provide effective funding software for our partners,” said FundRazr Founder and CEO Daryl Hatton.  “Healthline.com visitors can now raise funds to help address medical care bills, complete with coaching and support every step of the way.  We’ve already raised millions of dollars online for patient care and proven that patient’s online communities want to help with financial and moral support.”\r\n\r\n<strong>About Healthline</strong>\r\n\r\nSan Francisco-based Healthline is a leading provider of intelligent health information and technology solutions, enabling providers and everyday people to make more confident, informed healthcare decisions. The company\'s proprietary semantic health taxonomy platform powers a suite of marketing, health search, data-mining and content solutions for global enterprises and advertisers. Healthline is a Deloitte Technology Fast 500 company for the last four years. For more company information, visit <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com\">corp.healthline.com</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>About Powered by FundRazr</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://poweredby.fundrazr.com\">Powered By FundRazr</a> offers proven plug &amp; play crowdfunding technology for enterprise, institutions or high traffic websites.  We power your community’s funding needs while building community engagement.  Co-developed with PayPal, FundRazr has crowdfunded over $40M in 20 countries since 2010.  SETI, Save the Children and DC Entertainment, and Startup Weekend, have all been Powered By FundRazr.  The Powered By FundRazr crowdfunding-as-a-service solution was created in Vancouver, Canada and launched summer 2013.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" size=\"1\" width=\"33%\" />\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ednref1\">[i]</a> Sources:  “Medical Debt.” Retrieved from <a href=\"http://debt.org/medical\">http://debt.org/medical</a>; “NerdWallet Health finds Medical Bankruptcy accounts for majority of personal bankruptcies.”  Retrieved from <a href=\"http://www.nerdwallet.com/blog/health/2013/06/19/nerdwallet-health-study-estimates-56-million-americans-65-struggle-medical-bills-2013/\">http://www.nerdwallet.com/blog/health/2013/06/19/nerdwallet-health-study-estimates-56-million-americans-65-struggle-medical-bills-2013/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Healthline Introduces Medical Crowdfunding Powered by FundRazr—a New Way to Fund Medical Expenses ','','inherit','open','open','','142-autosave-v1','','','2014-02-11 19:27:43','2014-02-11 19:27:43','',142,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/142-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(153,4,'2014-02-14 15:30:40','2014-02-14 15:30:40','Healthcare brands looking to make connections with contextually relevant audiences really have to be thinking about mobile. Everything we know today points to one simple fact: if your brand isn\'t on mobile, you\'re not on the Internet.\n\nPharmaceutical marketers, in particular, need to confront radical changes in consumer health research behavior. Consider the following facts:\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Eight of the top ten health information publishers</strong> see more than 30% of unique visitors who are mobile-only.</li>\n	<li>On Healthline.com, <strong>46% of unique visitors view content exclusively from their mobile device</strong>, not from a desktop or laptop.</li>\n	<li>79% of traffic to Healthline.com\'s symptom checker is mobile, the beginning of treatment journey is through mobile.<a dir=\"ltr\" href=\"https://twitter.com/Kopportunity\">\n</a></li>\n	<li>Pharma brand names over index on mobile, condition treatment information does not.</li>\n	<li>The right way to engage with mobile is with content, not with banner ads.</li>\n	<li>If you do use banner ads, use non-flash creative as part of the media mix.  Thirty percent of mobile queries come from devices that are not Flash-enabled, reinforcing the need for creative developed outside of Flash.</li>\n</ul>\n<a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/why-mobile-matters-advertisers.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-137 alignleft\" alt=\"\" src=\"ht