dLab</a>','Top Five Social Trends for 2014','','inherit','open','open','','124-revision-v1','','','2014-02-14 15:44:51','2014-02-14 15:44:51','',124,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/124-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(165,2,'2014-02-17 16:02:04','2014-02-17 16:02:04','Healthline announced today the appointment of Scott Marber as Senior Vice President of Sales and Marketing for its Health Information &amp; Technology (HIT) Group, which powers search, data and content solutions for some of the world’s largest healthcare brands.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Healthline, Marber was senior vice president, sales and marketing, at Enclarity, recently acquired by LexisNexis. He brings more than 25 years of success in sales executive leadership roles at a number of companies that sell to the healthcare market. Through his leadership, Marber has generated more than $250 million in new revenue at the companies where he worked by introducing discipline and focus to the sales process.\r\n\r\n“Scott brings a wealth of experience and an impressive track record of results to the executive sales role in our fast-growing Health Information &amp; Technology Group,” said Dean Stephens, CEO of Healthline. “He also brings a real passion for the Healthline mission, which is to make the people of the world healthier through the power of information.”\r\n\r\nPrior to his work with Enclarity, Marber worked at Virgin HealthMiles, a wellness company founded by Sir Richard Branson of the Virgin Group, where he was senior vice president of sales, marketing the company’s services to major health plans and employers. Previously, Scott was senior vice president of sales and business development at Free &amp; Clear, which markets wellness services to employers, health plans and government agencies. In addition, Scott has led the growth of several health services organizations, ranging from start-ups to Fortune 500 companies.\r\n\r\n“The HIT Group at Healthline is pursuing an aggressive growth agenda and we’re excited that Scott will provide the necessary sales strategy and process framework to enable us to reach and exceed our goals,” said Niraj Katwala, CTO and General Manager of the Healthline HIT Group.\r\n\r\nA lifelong golfer who has played on four continents, Marber is a graduate of Dartmouth College and lives with his family in the Seattle, Washington area.\r\n\r\n<b>About Healthline</b>\r\n\r\nSan Francisco-based Healthline is a leading provider of intelligent health information and technology solutions, enabling payors, providers and everyday people to make more confident, informed healthcare decisions. The company\'s proprietary health taxonomy platform powers Healthline.com, and a suite of marketing, health search, data-mining and content solutions for global enterprises and advertisers. Healthline is a Deloitte Technology Fast 500 company for the last four years. For more company information, visit corp.healthline.com.','Scott Marber Joins Healthline to Lead Enterprise Sales Strategy ','','publish','closed','closed','','scott-marber-joins-healthline-to-lead-enterprise-sales-strategy','','','2014-02-17 16:02:04','2014-02-17 16:02:04','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?post_type=press_release&#038;p=165',0,'press_release','',0),(166,2,'2014-02-20 14:03:21','2014-02-20 14:03:21','<h4>Demonstrations of the Company’s Full Range of Health Information, Technology and Consumer Engagement Solutions to Occur in its Exhibit throughout the Conference</h4>\r\n<b>February 20, 2014—San Francisco, CA and Orlando, FL—</b>Healthline announces new <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/solutions/data/\">Data Solutions</a> for healthcare payors, providers, and other users of “big data” at the annual Health Information and Management Systems Society (HIMSS) 2014 <a href=\"http://www.himssconference.org/\">Conference and Exposition</a>. This year’s conference will be held at the Orange County Convention Center in Orlando, Florida February 23 - 27, 2014. Healthline can be found at booth 7273 in Hall E.\r\n\r\nCore to Healthline’s new Data Solutions offering is its Cohort Creation Engine<sup>SM</sup>, which enables the use of large sets of disparate data (both structured and unstructured) in a range of analytics applications. Healthline’s proprietary <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/platform/\">Semantic Taxonomy Platform</a> powers the Cohort Creation Engine™ and the company’s other HIT solutions for the enterprise.\r\n\r\n“Our curated taxonomy powers health information and technology solutions for some of the world’s largest healthcare organizations, delivering them better consumer engagement, improved health outcomes, and lower costs,” said Niraj Katwala, Chief Technology Officer at Healthline. “The demand for solutions that enable analysis of massive sets of disparate data is growing and we have figured out how to solve it.”\r\n\r\nThe Cohort Creation Engine<sup>SM</sup>, which can be deployed behind a firewall for safety and security,\r\n\r\nleverages a range of Healthline core technologies, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medically-Guided Search</li>\r\n	<li>Concept Indexing and Categorization</li>\r\n	<li>Natural Language Processing</li>\r\n	<li>Taxonomic Health Data Mapping</li>\r\n	<li>Analytics Engine API</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTogether, these technologies deliver a scalable solution that enables the clean delivery of massive data sets to reporting infrastructure, analytics engines, and data dashboards. Because this abstraction happens between the data source and the application, any new data source (e.g., EMR, etc.) can be added without having to reprogram reports.\r\n\r\n“Healthline’s Cohort Creation Engine aggregates data from disparate systems—clinical, administrative, claims, etc.—in various formats, including structured and unstructured data; categorizes and enriches it using Healthline’s unique taxonomy; and indexes it for precise, fast, and easy search and discovery,” said Murray Brozinsky, Chief Strategy Officer at Healthline. “The resulting cohorts provide rich data sets that can be used to power myriad applications, including patient engagement, clinical decision support, population health management, predictive modeling, and other high-value applications, as well as ad hoc queries.”\r\n\r\nHealthline will be demonstrating its <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/solutions/\">full range of consumer engagement and health information and technology solutions</a> at the HIMSS Conference, including its new Data Solutions. It is also unveiling a <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/welcome-to-a-new-healthline/\">new company identity</a> and corporate website at corp.healthline.com.\r\n\r\n“We\'ve proven the complex job of indexing vast quantities of unstructured content and delivering it contextually at the right time, to the right place, and in the right amount to physicians, patients, plan members and consumers,” said Dean Stephens, CEO and co-founder of Healthline. “The time has arrived to apply our dozen years of software development to conquering the task of uncovering insights from the growing mass of unstructured physician notes in EMRs and other emerging data and content storage vehicles.”\r\n\r\n<b>About Healthline</b>\r\n\r\nSan Francisco-based Healthline is a leading provider of intelligent health information and technology solutions, enabling payors, providers and everyday people to make more confident, informed healthcare decisions. The company\'s proprietary health taxonomy platform powers Healthline.com, and a suite of marketing, health search, data-mining and content solutions for global enterprises and advertisers. Healthline is a Deloitte Technology Fast 500 company for the last four years. For more company information, visit corp.healthline.com. <strong>Healthline: The Power of Intelligent Health</strong><sup>SM</sup><b>.</b>','Healthline to Unveil Healthcare “Big Data” Solutions at HIMSS 2014','','publish','closed','closed','','healthline-to-unveil-healthcare-big-data-solutions-at-himss-2014','','','2014-02-20 14:03:21','2014-02-20 14:03:21','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?post_type=press_release&#038;p=166',0,'press_release','',0),(167,2,'2014-02-19 15:25:35','2014-02-19 15:25:35','<h4>\"You Are Not Your COPD\" offers encouragement and support to those living with COPD</h4>\r\nHealthline announced the launch of an inspirational stories project today, “<a title=\"COPD Stories\" href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/copd/inspirational-stories\" rel=\"nofollow\">You Are Not Your COPD</a>,” in conjunction with the COPD Foundation to provide support and encouragement to those living with COPD. The project encourages individuals living with COPD to upload a photo of themselves together with a message letting the world know they are not defined by their disease. The stories will be posted on Healthline.com and will be shared on Healthline\'s Facebook page, <a title=\"Living with COPD\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Living-with-COPD/115563115238459?ref=hl\" rel=\"nofollow\">Living with COPD</a>.\r\n\r\nHealthline will donate $10 to the COPD Foundation for every submission, with a goal of donating $5,000 total. People are encouraged to browse and share the submitted photos—Healthline’s editorial team will choose a winner from the top five most shared entries to win a $75 American Express gift card.\r\n\r\n\"People living with COPD need understanding and support,\" said John W. Walsh, president and co-founder of the COPD Foundation. \"Healthline\'s project encourages the entire COPD community to get involved, from the newly diagnosed to the patient who has been living with COPD for years. We believe it will be inspirational, informative, and engaging.\"\r\n\r\nCOPD, a condition that includes chronic bronchitis and emphysema, is the third leading cause of death in the U.S. More than 24 million Americans have COPD, and researchers believe half of those people—12 million—remain undiagnosed.\r\n\r\n“So many people living with COPD are anxious and unsure of the future,” said Tracy Rosecrans, Vice President of Marketing for the Healthline Media Group. \"This initiative is meant to provide them with some hope and a strong sense of community. Individuals can learn to not let their condition define them and live life to the fullest by reading these inspirational stories written by others living with COPD.\"\r\n\r\nAnyone can submit a “You Are Not Your COPD” message. To participate, download a placard at \"<a title=\"COPD stories\" href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/copd/inspirational-stories\" rel=\"nofollow\">You Are Not Your COPD</a>.” Take a picture of yourself holding the card, and write a couple of sentences about why COPD doesn\'t define you.\r\n\r\n“Tell us who you are and what you like to do,” Rosecrans advises. “Are you a mother? An artist? Describe what you\'ve been able to accomplish while living with COPD.”\r\n\r\nTo submit your entry, view entries from other COPD patients, and learn more, visit: <a title=\"people with copd\" href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/copd/inspirational-stories\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.healthline.com/health/copd/inspirational-stories</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>About Healthline </strong>\r\nSan Francisco-based Healthline is a leading provider of intelligent health information and technology solutions, enabling providers and everyday people to make more confident, informed healthcare decisions. The company\'s proprietary semantic health taxonomy platform powers a suite of marketing, health search, data-mining and content solutions for global enterprises and advertisers. Healthline is a Deloitte Technology Fast 500 company for the last four years. For more company information, visit corp.healthline.com.\r\n\r\n<strong>About the COPD Foundation </strong>\r\nCelebrating its 10th Anniversary and a decade of progress, the mission of the COPD Foundation (<a title=\"COPD Foundation\" href=\"http://www.copdfoundation.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.copdfoundation.org</a>) is to prevent and cure chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and to improve the lives of all people affected by COPD. The C.O.P.D. Information Line, 866-316-COPD (2673), is a toll-free number for information and referrals on COPD, offering callers access to peer-to-peer patients and caregiver associates.','Healthline Partners with COPD Foundation to Launch Inspirational Stories Project','','publish','closed','closed','','healthline-partners-with-copd-foundation-to-launch-inspirational-stories-project','','','2014-02-19 15:25:35','2014-02-19 15:25:35','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?post_type=press_release&#038;p=167',0,'press_release','',0),(168,5,'2014-02-20 14:00:23','2014-02-20 14:00:23','Healthline <a href=\"http://www.prweb.com/releases/2014/02/prweb11594370.htm\">announced</a> today its new Data Solutions offering, which we will debut at the upcoming <a href=\"http://www.himssconference.org/\">HIMSS 2014 Conference</a>.\r\n\r\nDigital health and wellness data is being generated at an unprecedented rate. Electronic Medical Records (EMRs) and other clinical systems, administrative systems, health claims, consumer tracking devices &amp; wearables, genomics, and other sources will create more than 20 exabytes of data by 2020, more than 500 times the entire written works of humankind since recorded history. Unfortunately, most healthcare organizations (HCOs) aren’t tapping this wealth of knowledge. In a world of big data, most HCOs are operating on small data.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-368\" alt=\"data value\" src=\"http://healthline.dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/data-data-value.png\" width=\"271\" height=\"271\" />\r\n\r\nThis widening gap between data and usable data is driving demand for solutions that can deal with the volume, variety, and velocity to make data actionable.. Healthline’s Data Solutions are purpose-built to address this demand.\r\n\r\nThe core of Healthline’s Data Solutions is the Cohort Creation Engine<sup>SM</sup>, which enables the use of large sets of disparate data in a range of applications. The Cohort Creation Engine aggregates data from disparate systems—clinical, administrative, claims, etc.—in various formats, including structured and unstructured data; categorizes and enriches it using Healthline’s unique taxonomy; and indexes it for precise, fast,, easy search &amp; discovery.\r\n\r\nThe resulting cohorts provide rich data sets that can be used to power myriad applications, including patient engagement, clinical decision support, population health management, predictive modeling, and other high-value applications, as well as ad hoc queries.\r\n\r\nThe Cohort Creation Engine leverages a range of Healthline’s core technologies, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medically-Guided Search</li>\r\n	<li>Concept Indexing and Categorization</li>\r\n	<li>Natural Language Processing</li>\r\n	<li>Taxonomic Health Data Mapping</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUnderlying these technologies is Healthline’s <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/platform/\">semantic health taxonomy</a>, which powers health information and technology solutions for major healthcare organizations, helping them achieve better engagement, improved patient outcomes, and lower costs.\r\n\r\nThe Cohort Creation Engine can be deployed as a cloud-based service or behind a firewall for safety and security.\r\n\r\nWe’re are very excited about the potential for our Data Solutions to enable healthcare enterprises to realize the promise of data-driven healthcare.','Helping to Fill Big Gaps in Healthcare with “Big Data”','','publish','open','open','','helping-to-fill-big-gaps-in-healthcare-with-big-data','','','2014-04-02 11:40:56','2014-04-02 18:40:56','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?p=168',0,'post','',0),(169,2,'2014-02-19 17:19:19','2014-02-19 17:19:19','','health-data-sources','','inherit','open','open','','health-data-sources','','','2014-02-19 17:19:19','2014-02-19 17:19:19','',168,'http://corp.health