le have amazing stories to tell. Content curating bubbles up <a href=\"http://corp-stage.healthline.com/blog/top-five-social-trends-for-2014/\">remarkable content,</a> and social provides a megaphone to share it. Most importantly, the “You’ve Got This” videos provided hope. Newly diagnosed patients and sufferers want to to feel they are not alone, and want to hear “You’ve Got This’.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWant more Healthline Media Group insights and news? Follow us on Twitter: <a href=\"https://twitter.com/HealthlineAdLab\">@HealthlineAdLab</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','','','inherit','open','open','','183-revision-v1','','','2014-03-20 12:08:15','2014-03-20 19:08:15','',183,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/183-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(185,4,'2014-03-20 12:08:42','2014-03-20 19:08:42','The diagnosis of a disease or condition is a serious and scary thing to face. Sometimes, this can leave people feeling alone. But they need to know that they’re not alone. They need to hear “You’ve Got This.”\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;Embed video &gt; You’ve Got This: <a href=\"http://vimeo.com/88770480\">http://vimeo.com/88770480</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>What It Is:</b>\r\n\r\nThe “You’ve Got This” program illuminates how social provides meaningful value to the health-seeking Internet user. “You’ve Got This” is a powerful <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/about-us/press-releases/healthline-launches-new-public-service-initiative-with-the-national-ms-society/\">public service initiative</a> that gives hope to individuals recently diagnosed with a condition.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe launched our first “You’ve Got This” program in August 2013. The <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/hiv-aids/youve-got-this\">“You’ve Got This” HIV</a> program gained lots of social buzz. After overwhelmingly positive feedback with patients and advocates alike, as well as major news media pick up, we followed up with a <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youv