pen','','214-revision-v1','','','2014-04-01 16:43:35','2014-04-01 23:43:35','',214,'http://healthline.dev/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(407,1,'2014-04-01 16:44:48','2014-04-01 23:44:48','','Search & Discovery Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','214-revision-v1','','','2014-04-01 16:44:48','2014-04-01 23:44:48','',214,'http://healthline.dev/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(408,1,'2014-04-01 16:45:36','2014-04-01 23:45:36','','Search & Discovery Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','214-revision-v1','','','2014-04-01 16:45:36','2014-04-01 23:45:36','',214,'http://healthline.dev/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(409,1,'2014-04-01 16:53:39','2014-04-01 23:53:39','','Search & Discovery Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','214-revision-v1','','','2014-04-01 16:53:39','2014-04-01 23:53:39','',214,'http://healthline.dev/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(410,1,'2014-04-02 11:40:56','2014-04-02 18:40:56','Healthline <a href=\"http://www.prweb.com/releases/2014/02/prweb11594370.htm\">announced</a> today its new Data Solutions offering, which we will debut at the upcoming <a href=\"http://www.himssconference.org/\">HIMSS 2014 Conference</a>.\r\n\r\nDigital health and wellness data is being generated at an unprecedented rate. Electronic Medical Records (EMRs) and other clinical systems, administrative systems, health claims, consumer tracking devices &amp; wearables, genomics, and other sources will create more than 20 exabytes of data by 2020, more than 500 times the entire written works of humankind since recorded history. Unfortunately, most healthcare organizations (HCOs) aren’t tapping this wealth of knowledge. In a world of big data, most HCOs are operating on small data.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-368\" alt=\"data value\" src=\"http://healthline.dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/data-data-value.png\" width=\"271\" height=\"271\" />\r\n\r\nThis widening gap between data and usable data is driving demand for solutions that can deal with the volume, variety, and velocity to make data actionable.. Healthline’s Data Solutions are purpose-built to address this demand.\r\n\r\nThe core of Healthline’s Data Solutions is the Cohort Creation Engine<sup>SM</sup>, which enables the use of large sets of disparate data in a range of applications. The Cohort Creation Engine aggregates data from disparate systems—clinical, administrative, claims, etc.—in various formats, including structured and unstructured data; categorizes and enriches it using Healthline’s unique taxonomy; and indexes it for precise, fast,, easy search &amp; discovery.\r\n\r\nThe resulting cohorts provide rich data sets that can be used to power myriad applications, including patient engagement, clinical decision support, population health management, predictive modeling, and other high-value applications, as well as ad hoc queries.\r\n\r\nThe Cohort Creation Engine leverages a range of Healthline’s core technologies, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medically-Guided Search</li>\r\n	<li>Concept Indexing and Categorization</li>\r\n	<li>Natural Language Processing</li>\r\n	<li>Taxonomic Health Data Mapping</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUnderlying these technologies is Healthline’s <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/platform/\">semantic health taxonomy</a>, which powers health information and technology solutions for major healthcare organizations, helping them achieve better engagement, improved patient outcomes, and lower costs.\r\n\r\nThe Cohort Creation Engine can be deployed as a cloud-based service or behind a firewall for safety and security.\r\n\r\nWe’re are very excited about the potential for our Data Solutions to enable healthcare enterprises to realize the promise of data-driven healthcare.','Helping to Fill Big Gaps in Healthcare with “Big Data”','','inherit','open','open','','168-revision-v1','','','2014-04-02 11:40:56','2014-04-02 18:40:56','',168,'http://healthline.dev/168-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(411,1,'2014-04-02 11:42:28','2014-04-02 18:42:28','','MSFT Bing Health Fitness App','','inherit','open','open','','msft-bing-health-fitness-app-healthline-690x387','','','2014-04-02 11:42:28','2014-04-02 18:42:28','',145,'http://healthline.dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MSFT-Bing-Health-Fitness-App-Healthline-690x387.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(412,1,'2014-04-02 11:43:55','2014-04-02 18:43:55','','Healthline Logo','','inherit','open','open','','healthline-logo-3','','','2014-04-02 11:43:55','2014-04-02 18:43:55','',119,'http://healthline.dev/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Healthline-Logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(413,1,'2014-04-02 11:46:00','2014-04-02 18:46:00','The diagnosis of a disease or condition is a serious and scary thing to face. Sometimes, this can leave people feeling alone. But they need to know that they’re not alone. They need to hear “You’ve Got This.”\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/88770480\" height=\"385\" width=\"643\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\" target=\"_blank\">You Got This </a>from <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com\" target=\"_blank\">Healthline</a>\r\n\r\n<b><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">What It Is:</span></b>\r\n\r\nThe “You’ve Got This” program illuminates how social provides meaningful value to the health-seeking Internet user. This powerful <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/about-us/press-releases/healthline-launches-new-public-service-initiative-with-the-national-ms-society/\" target=\"_blank\"> public service initiative</a> gives hope to individuals recently diagnosed with a condition.\r\n\r\nWe launched our first “You’ve Got This” program in August 2013. The <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/hiv-aids/youve-got-this\" target=\"_blank\">“You’ve Got This” HIV</a> program gained lots of social buzz. After overwhelmingly positive feedback with patients and advocates alike, as well as major news media pick up, we followed up with a <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\" target=\"_blank\">“You’ve Got This” MS</a>, and we are actively building a Bipolar version too.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Sharing Safe Social With Rx and Health Advertisers:</b>\r\n\r\nHealthline’s had a lot of success in social (as a publisher) and has increasingly been able to bring pharma advertisers into those moments of connection. Instead of trying to push pharma into the conversations, we pull out the conversations happening in social. Our editors then curate and package this video content within our site. Advertisers have the opportunity to sponsor these safe, socially inspired video programs, aligning with community influencers and supportive patient stories.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">How It Works:</b>\r\n\r\nHealthline’s condition-specific <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\">Facebook pages</a> feature a call out, asking those living with the condition to send in a video providing advice to someone recently diagnosed. Healthline curates the submitted videos and posts them to our website. We then share the videos on Facebook and spread the word back to the community.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Why It Works:</b>\r\n\r\nPeople have amazing stories to tell. Content curation bubbles up <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/top-five-social-trends-for-2014/\" target=\"_blank\">remarkable content,</a> and social provides a megaphone to share it. Most importantly, the “You’ve Got This” videos provided hope. Newly diagnosed patients and sufferers want to to feel they are not alone, and want to hear “You’ve Got This’.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Want more Healthline Media Group insights and news? Follow us on Twitter: </span><a style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/HealthlineAdLab\" target=\"_blank\">@HealthlineAdLab</a>','Welcoming Pharma Advertisers to Socially Inspired Video Content','','inherit','open','open','','183-revision-v1','','','2014-04-02 11:46:00','2014-04-02 18:46:00','',183,'http://healthline.dev/183-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(414,1,'2014-04-02 11:46:26','2014-04-02 18:46:26','The diagnosis of a disease or condition is a serious and scary thing to face. Sometimes, this can leave people feeling alone. But they need to know that they’re not alone. They need to hear “You’ve Got This.”\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/88770480\" height=\"405\" width=\"643\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\" target=\"_blank\">You Got This </a>from <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com\" target=\"_blank\">Healthline</a>\r\n\r\n<b><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">What It Is:</span></b>\r\n\r\nThe “You’ve Got This” program illuminates how social provides meaningful value to the health-seeking Internet user. This powerful <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/about-us/press-releases/healthline-launches-new-public-service-initiative-with-the-national-ms-society/\" target=\"_blank\"> public service initiative</a> gives hope to individuals recently diagnosed with a condition.\r\n\r\nWe launched our first “You’ve Got This” program in August 2013. The <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/hiv-aids/youve-got-this\" target=\"_blank\">“You’ve Got This” HIV</a> program gained lots of social buzz. After overwhelmingly positive feedback with patients and advocates alike, as well as major news media pick up, we followed up with a <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\" target=\"_blank\">“You’ve Got This” MS</a>, and we are actively building a Bipolar version too.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Sharing Safe Social With Rx and Health Advertisers:</b>\r\n\r\nHealthline’s had a lot of success in social (as a publisher) and has increasingly been able to bring pharma advertisers into those moments of connection. Instead of trying to push pharma into the conversations, we pull out the conversations happening in social. Our editors then curate and package this video content within our site. Advertisers have the opportunity to sponsor these safe, socially inspired video programs, aligning with community influencers and supportive patient stories.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">How It Works:</b>\r\n\r\nHealthline’s condition-specific <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\">Facebook pages</a> feature a call out, asking those living with the condition to send in a video providing advice to someone recently diagnosed. Healthline curates the submitted videos and posts them to our website. We then share the videos on Facebook and spread the word back to the community.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Why It Works:</b>\r\n\r\nPeople have amazing stories to tell. Content curation bubbles up <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/top-five-social-trends-for-2014/\" target=\"_blank\">remarkable content,</a> and social provides a megaphone to share it. Most importantly, the “You’ve Got This” videos provided hope. Newly diagnosed patients and sufferers want to to feel they are not alone, and want to hear “You’ve Got This’.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Want more Healthline Media Group insights and news? Follow us on Twitter: </span><a style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/HealthlineAdLab\" target=\"_blank\">@HealthlineAdLab</a>','Welcoming Pharma Advertisers to Socially Inspired Video Content','','inherit','open','open','','183-revision-v1','','','2014-04-02 11:46:26','2014-04-02 18:46:26','',183,'http://healthline.dev/183-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(415,1